The paper discusses medical image segmentation using deep learning, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs). This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of modernization techniques such as ReLU activation and dropout layers, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the use of multi-pathway settings is a common technique in neural network (cs.NE) research. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging (cs.MM), which is another likely sub-category.
